item.title: Is Big Ten football more competitive in the Scott Frost era?
item.description: Is Big Ten football more competitive in the Scott Frost Era than the Bo Pelini Era? Since Nebraska joined the Big Ten in 2011, Pelini is the only Husker head coach to win 10 or more games in a season and the only coach to win nine games in a season multiple times. When Peliniâ€™s seven-season reign was ended after the 2014 season, Mike Riley was hired and went 19-19 in three seasons.
